Adventa, PLDT, Singapore Airlines: Asia Ex-Japan Equity Preview

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-06-30T00:28:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-30/adventa-pldt-singapore-airlines-asia-ex-japan-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Asian trading, excluding Japan.
Stock symbols are in parentheses and share prices are from the
previous close, unless noted otherwise.  Adventa Bhd. (ADV)  : The rubber glove maker’s profit in
the second quarter ended April 30 dropped 29 percent from a year
earlier to 4.59 million ringgit ($1.5 million), according to a
company statement. The stock fell 2.5 percent to 1.95 ringgit.  George Kent  (Malaysia) Bhd. (GKEN MK): The Malaysian water
treatment company and supplier of water tanks said profit in the
first quarter ended April 30 rose 9.8 percent from a year
earlier to 3.07 million ringgit, according to a stock filing.
George Kent was unchanged at 1.15 ringgit.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  : The
Philippine Stock Exchange Inc. said a Supreme Court decision
ordering a probe into Philippine Long Distance’s foreign
ownership may spur capital flight and discourage investment.  The court directed the Securities and Exchange Commission
to investigate the company known as PLDT for possible violation
of the 40 percent constitutional limit on foreign ownership,
according to the decision released yesterday. PLDT, the nation’s
largest phone company, dropped 3.2 percent to 2,324 pesos.  Singapore Airlines Ltd. (SIA)  : The world’s second-
largest carrier by market value agreed to lease an additional 15
Airbus SAS A330-300 planes as it seeks growth in Asia, Australia
and the  Middle East . Shares of the carrier added 0.3 percent to
S$14.28.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
